<p>Need help to solve the validation problem with jquery validator. </p>  <p>On click of table div element, yes no option displayed. Here $(this).data() is table column data</p>  <pre><code> $(tableId).on('click', '.Copy', function (e) {     var data = $(this).data();     $('&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Are you sure you wish to Copy?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;').dialog({         title: 'Copy',         modal: true,         resizable: false,         draggable: false,         closeOnEscape: true,         buttons: [             {                 text: 'Yes',                 click: function () {                     formIdentifier = data.Identifier;                     $dlgOptions.dialog('open');                     $(this).dialog('destroy');                 }             },             {                 text: 'No',                 click: function () {                     $(this).dialog('destroy');                 }             }         ]     });   }); </code></pre>  <p>Once you click yes - html dialog opens. here is the html part of the dialog.</p>  <pre><code>&lt;form novalidate="novalidate" id="Copy-form"&gt;  &lt;div class="col full"&gt;   &lt;label class="form-label" for="Copy-new-identifier"&gt;Copy Identifier&lt;/label&gt;      &lt;input id="form-new-identifier" name="NewCopyIdentifier" type="text"&gt;  &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/form&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Here is my validator initiated with rules, message to display and submit handler.</p>  <pre><code> var CopyFormValidator = $('#Copy-form').validate({     rules: {         'NewCopyIdentifier': {             required: true,             maxlength: 6,             minlength: 6,             remote: {                 url: '/api/validate/validate-identifier',                 type: 'POST',                 dataType: 'json',                 cache: false,                 data: {                     Identifier: function () {                         return $('#form-new-identifier').val();                     }                 }             }       